In this proclamation, President Barack Obama recognizes Veterans Day and honors the men and women who have served in the Armed Forces. He emphasizes the importance of expressing gratitude to veterans for their sacrifices and ensuring they have access to resources and education when they return home. The President highlights the progress made in reducing veteran homelessness and improving employment opportunities for veterans. He also emphasizes the need to provide high-quality healthcare to veterans. President Obama calls on Americans to uphold their obligations to veterans and never forget those who have paid the ultimate price for liberty. He proclaims November 11, 2016, as Veterans Day and encourages public ceremonies, private prayers, and commemorative expressions to honor veterans.